-- XL Axiata sets share sale price at minimum 5,280 rupiah apiece
-- By Fransiska Nangoy
-- Thu Jun 26, 2014 04:56AM EDT
-- None



JAKARTA, June 26 (Reuters) - PT XL Axiata Tbk <EXCL.JK>, Indonesia's second-largest telecommunication company by subscribers, on Thursday set a minimum price of 5,280 rupiah ($0.45) per share for its sale of 231.1 million shares.

"At the moment, the price (in the market) is below that, we will not sell yet," said CEO Hasnul Suhaimi. XL Axiata shares were up 3.5 percent at 5,075 rupiah as of 0850 GMT. In a filing to the Indonesia Stock Exchange, the company also said it secured a $100 million loan from United Overseas Bank Ltd <UOBH.SI>. The loan will be used for capital expansion and refinancing.